 {"id":"franken_numpy-xfdw","title":"Add 12+ oracle-verified reduction edge-case fixtures to ufunc differential corpus","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-06T21:37:33.066647567Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-06T23:23:51.707191405Z","closed_at":"2026-04-06T23:23:51.706939247Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","ufunc"],"comments":[{"id":9,"issue_id":"franken_numpy-xfdw","author":"ubuntu","text":"Expand the ufunc_differential.rs oracle capture to include edge cases that are known to diverge between Rust float semantics and NumPy C semantics. Priority cases: (1) reduce_sum/prod on empty arrays (NumPy returns 0.0/1.0), (2) reduce_min/max on single-element arrays, (3) reduce_mean/var/std on all-NaN arrays, (4) multi-axis reductions like np.sum(x, axis=(0,2)). These are tested by our own tests but NOT verified against the NumPy oracle.","created_at":"2026-04-06T21:39:00Z"},{"id":18,"issue_id":"franken_numpy-xfdw","author":"ubuntu","text":"REVISION (plan-space refinement round 1):\n\nWHERE: Add fixtures to artifacts/fixtures/ufunc_differential_cases.json (or create new fixture file artifacts/fixtures/ufunc_reduction_edge_cases.json). Add corresponding Rust test(s) in crates/fnp-conformance/src/lib.rs under the existing ufunc_metamorphic or differential test section.\n\nEXACT TEST CASES TO ADD (each must be oracle-captured against real NumPy):\n1. np.sum(np.array([], dtype=float64)) → 0.0\n2. np.prod(np.array([], dtype=float64)) → 1.0\n3. np.mean(np.array([], dtype=float64)) → RuntimeWarning + nan\n4. np.min(np.array([42.0])) → 42.0 (single element)\n5. np.max(np.array([42.0])) → 42.0 (single element)\n6. np.mean(np.array([nan, nan, nan])) → nan\n7. np.var(np.array([nan, nan, nan])) → nan\n8. np.std(np.array([nan, nan, nan]), ddof=1) → nan\n9. np.sum(np.arange(24).reshape(2,3,4), axis=(0,2)) → shape (3,) multi-axis\n10. np.prod(np.ones((2,3,4)), axis=(0,2)) → shape (3,) all 1.0\n11. np.sum(np.array([1e308, 1e308])) → inf (overflow)\n12. np.sum(np.array([1e-308, -1e-308])) → 0.0 (cancellation)\n\nVALIDATION: Each fixture runs through the oracle capture script (PY_CAPTURE_SCRIPT in ufunc_differential.rs), compares FrankenNumPy output to NumPy output. Shape, dtype, and values must match within tolerance (1e-12 for float64).\n\nLOGGING: Each test case should print the fixture ID, expected vs actual values, and pass/fail status to stderr when run with --nocapture.\n\nACCEPTANCE: All 12+ fixtures pass differential comparison. No regressions in existing 119 conformance tests.","created_at":"2026-04-06T23:04:26Z"}]}
